From John Nagle Subject Re Key Registering Bodies Since the law requires that wiretaps be requested by the Executive Branch and approved by the Judicial Branch it seems clear that one of the key registering bodies should be under the control of the Judicial I suggest the Supreme Court or regionally the Courts of More specifically the offices of their Courts already operate substantial record keeping Some of these records are So the concept of a court holding information in confidence in accordance with law has longstanding legal The judiciary is more immune to pressure from the executive branch than any executive branch agency or contractor can So judicial control of keys is For the other half of the key I suggest a unit of Congress the General Accounting The GAO is Congress's staff unit for keeping tabs on the Executive Branch and has an excellent It's controlled strictly by Congress the Executive Branch has no authority over With keys split between the Legislative and Judicial branches we might have a chance of this system working If of course a way can be found to keep the keys from being siphoned off before they reach the This should not be construed as an endorsement by me of the whole Clipper But if we have to have it splitting control across all three branches of government might make it John Nagle